<question type="stack">
  <name><text>Week 14 – Q2: Wave Parameters and Reflection at Media Boundary</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[
<p>A signal at frequency \(f = {@f_GHz@}\) GHz propagates from <b>Medium 1</b> (\(\varepsilon_{r1} = {@eps_r1@}\), non-magnetic, lossless) into <b>Medium 2</b> (\(\varepsilon_{r2} = {@eps_r2@}\), non-magnetic, lossless) at normal incidence.</p>

<p><b>(a)</b> Phase velocity in Medium 1: \(v_{p1} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] m/s</p>

<p><b>(b)</b> Wavelength in Medium 1: \(\lambda_1 = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] m</p>

<p><b>(c)</b> Wavenumber in Medium 1: \(k_1 = 2\pi/\lambda_1 = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] rad/m</p>

<p><b>(d)</b> Intrinsic impedance of Medium 1: \(\eta_1 = \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] \(\Omega\)</p>

<p><b>(e)</b> Intrinsic impedance of Medium 2: \(\eta_2 = \) [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] \(\Omega\)</p>

<p><b>(f)</b> Reflection coefficient at the boundary (Medium 1 incident): \(\Gamma = \) [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]]</p>

<p><b>(g)</b> Reflected power fraction: \(|\Gamma|^2 = \) [[input:ans7]] [[validation:ans7]]</p>
]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[
<h4>Worked Solution</h4>
<p><b>Given:</b> \(f = {@f_GHz@}\) GHz, \(\varepsilon_{r1} = {@eps_r1@}\), \(\varepsilon_{r2} = {@eps_r2@}\), both non-magnetic and lossless.</p>
<p><b>(a)</b> \(v_{p1} = c/\sqrt{\varepsilon_{r1}} = {@tans1@}\) m/s</p>
<p><b>(b)</b> \(\lambda_1 = v_{p1}/f = {@tans2@}\) m</p>
<p><b>(c)</b> \(k_1 = 2\pi/\lambda_1 = {@tans3@}\) rad/m</p>
<p><b>(d)</b> \(\eta_1 = 120\pi/\sqrt{\varepsilon_{r1}} = {@tans4@}\;\Omega\)</p>
<p><b>(e)</b> \(\eta_2 = 120\pi/\sqrt{\varepsilon_{r2}} = {@tans5@}\;\Omega\)</p>
<p><b>(f)</b> \(\Gamma = (\eta_2 - \eta_1)/(\eta_2 + \eta_1) = {@tans6@}\). Negative because \(\varepsilon_{r2} > \varepsilon_{r1}\) makes \(\eta_2 < \eta_1\).</p>
<p><b>(g)</b> \(|\Gamma|^2 = {@tans7@}\) ({@float(tans7*100)@}% reflected, {@float((1-tans7)*100)@}% transmitted).</p>
]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
